qas.question: What is the head of government's office called in Canada?
What is the head of government's office called in the UK?
What is the Cabinet in Canada?
What never includes the role of Cabinet?

context: The Prime Minister's <b2_0>executive office<b2_0/> is usually called the <a0_0>Office of the Prime Minister<a0_0/> in the case of the Canada and other Commonwealth countries, it is called <a1_0>Cabinet Office<a1_0/> in United Kingdom. Some <b3_0>Prime Minister's office<b3_0/> do include the role of Cabinet. In other countries, it is called the Prime Minister's Department or the Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet as for Australia.
